  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "With regards to the existing literature, we reviewed the most recent and/or highly cited articles on data harmonization in a wide variety of fields, including geography (e.g.",
    "soil maps 24, land-use maps 25), health (e.g.",
    "epidemiology 20, medical imaging 26, electronic medical records 27), social sciences (e.g.",
    "economic indicators 4, 5, demography 28), ultimately resulting in around 100 studies.",
    "By considering lessons for data harmonization across a broad number of subject areas, we both distill issues common to many of them while further elucidating perspectives that data scientists may otherwise not come across if narrowly focused within their own field of study."
  ],
